    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once brown, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>black bean paste </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) then cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to the dish</p><p>Give everything a good mix up</p>",
